This paper focuses on developing a behavioral approach for visual navigation using topological maps, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using graph neural networks for localizing the agent in the map, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of primitive behaviors implemented as convolutional or recurrent neural networks, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.LG and cs.SY.
